{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01DfouT5KtTzr8nsosqCBVys","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The rolling restart is stuck because crdb-cluster-2 (with new certs) can't form quorum with crdb-cluster-0 and crdb-cluster-1 (with old certs). Since both old and new certs are from the same CA, there must be something else going on.\n\nLet me think again. The rolling restart is waiting for crdb-cluster-2 to become ready. It can't restart crdb-cluster-1 until crdb-cluster-2 is ready. But crdb-cluster-2 needs to gossip with crdb-cluster-0 and crdb-cluster-1 to become ready, and the TLS handshake is failing.\nActually, I think I see the issue now. When I restarted crdb-cluster-2, it picked up the new ca.crt from the secret, but pods 0 and 1 are still running with the old ca.crt they loaded at startup. Kubernetes does refresh mounted secrets dynamically, but CockroachDB might not be re-reading them automatically. If it doesn't reload certs on the fly, then pods 0 and 1 are stuck with the old CA and can't validate crdb-cluster-2's new certificate.\n\nBut wait—if I used the same ca.crt from the toolbox, it should still work even if pods 0 and 1 haven't refreshed. Unless the ca.crt in the toolbox is actually different from what was originally in the secret. I need to decode the current ca.crt from the secret and compare it with the toolbox version to see if they match.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1439,"cache_read_input_tokens":54270,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1439},"output_tokens":23,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9db65659-7646-4124-8edc-f420fd8e6e18","uuid":"3f090aca-da7b-498d-b401-45edfc070b01","request_id":"req_011CcekoZUkg2rgAmdQ5ipDA